‘Quod tamen nemo‚' &c. Cicero very frequently uses ‘id,' ‘illud,' ‘hoc,' with reference to something that he is going to say. He uses ‘quod’ just in the same way, ‘quod’ being in fact a demonstrative in its original. No person can take ‘ quod’ for what they call a conjunction here. ‘Tamen' forbids that. Examples of this form of expression are common.
